=pod

=encoding UTF-8

=head1 NAME

show-border-style - Show example table with specified border style

=head1 VERSION

This document describes version 0.012 of show-border-style (from Perl distribution App-BorderStyleUtils), released on 2021-04-24.

=head1 SYNOPSIS

Usage:

 % show-border-style [--debug] [--format=name] [--json] [--log-level=level]
     [--(no)naked-res] [--page-result[=program]] [--quiet] [--trace]
     [--verbose] [--view-result[=program]] <style>

Examples:

Show the details for the ASCII::SingleLineDoubleAfterHeader border style:

 % show-border-style ASCII::SingleLineDoubleAfterHeader
 # Positions for border character
 
  ---------------------------------------------
  y\x  0    1    2    3    4    5    6    7
   0  '.'  '-'  '+'  '.'                              <--- top border
   1  '|'  '|'  '|'                                   <--- header row
   2  '+'  '='  '+'  '+'  '+'  '+'                    <--- separator between header & data row
   3  '|'  '|'  '|'                                   <--- data row
   4  '+'  '-'  '+'  '+'  '+'  '+'  '+'  '+'          <--- separator between data rows
   5  '`'  '-'  '+'  '''                              <--- bottom border
 
   6  ''  ''  ''  ''                              <--- top border (for case when there is no header row)
   7  ''  ''  ''  ''                              <--- bottom border (for case when there is header row but no data row)
  ---------------------------------------------
 
 .--------+--------.     #
 | header | header |     #
 +========+========+     #
 | cell   | cell   |     # Table with header row, without row/column spans
 +--------+--------+     #
 | cell   | cell   |     #
 `--------+--------'     #
 
      #
 | cell   | cell   |     # Table without header row, with data rows
 +--------+--------+     #
 | cell   | cell   |     #
 `--------+--------'     #
 
 .--------+--------.     #
 | header | header |     # Table with header row, but without any data row
      #
 
 .-----------+-----+-----.     #
 | header    | hea | hea |     #
 +=====+=====+=====+=====+     #
 | cel | cel | cell      |     #
 +-----+-----+-----+-----+     #
 | cell      | cel | cel |     #
 +-----------+-----+-----+     # Table with row/column spans
 | cell      | cell      |     #
 |           +-----------+     #
 |           | cell      |     #
 +-----------+           |     #
 | cell      |           |     #
 `-----------+-----------'     #

=head1 OPTIONS

C<*> marks required options.

